    # game/areas/howlersdell2thais.rpy:106
    old "She’s sitting on a chair with a four-year-old boy on her knees - she’s holding his hand gently, showing him how to eat gruel from a bowl. It’s not a {i}cheap{/i} meal, though - you spot nuts, berries, and milk, and the added honey makes it yellowish. The kid is clean and quiet, and once he notices your arrival, he crams his mouth with a spoonful of oats. \n\n“Now, now, love,” {color=#f6d6bd}the mayor{/color} titters, “do ne get {i}distracted{/i},” she rubs the meal off his face. “A few more spoons en you’ll go help papa in the kitchen, aye?” She gives you a radiant, though apologetic, smile, then turns her attention back to her companion. "
