    # game/areas/howlersdell2thais.rpy:780
    old "{color=#f6d6bd}Thais{/color} spares you but a harsh glance. “Yes?” "
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell2thais.rpy:794
    old "“I wonder... Back in {color=#f6d6bd}Hovlavan{/color}, did you spend any time in Backwood Corner? It used to be this dark, dirty alley, with muggers {i}working{/i} even in daylight. I stayed there with Octavia, the miller, in exchange for doing chores for her. She had this small, wooden hut.” "
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell2thais.rpy:794
    old "“Since the war, even the soldiers have avoided that street. People say it’s a home for thugs.”"
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell2thais.rpy:794
    old "“You wouldn’t recognize it. It’s now a respectable street, with one of the fanciest inns in the city - The Apple And The Boar.”"
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell2thais.rpy:794
    old "“It would make you feel like you’re in the old days. The Boarhead Inn is almost fifty years old, now.”"
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell2thais.rpy:794
    old "“There’s no such street anymore. It fell to a great fire.”"
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell2thais.rpy:801
    old "“Oh dear, is that so? Maybe it was bound to happen. Kindness and hospitality don’t bloom in days of hunger. I hope the good old lady of The Boarhead Inn didn’t have to see that. She did her best to keep the children off the street, it must have been heartbreaking to see them turn against each other.” "
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell2thais.rpy:810
    old "You describe how a family of Southerners started a large shipyard right next to the alley, working on exotic boats in unusual shapes. Needing hands to work, they offered food and coins to many local thugs, and with time, more light and stalls showed up in the alley. \n\nAs you describe the new inn, {color=#f6d6bd}Thais{/color} bursts into cheerful laughter. “So it’s the same family that ran The Boarhead Inn? And to think that I dared to doubt the old lady’s endurance! People like her, brave enough to bear the toil of their world, are going to bring salvation to all of us.” "
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell2thais.rpy:820
    old "You explain that while the place is still called the {i}bad{/i} part of the city, The Boarhead makes good coin selling beer and ale to students, mercenaries, and adventurers. “The whole Land may turn wild one day,” you quote one of the local traders, “but Backwood Corner will stay the same.” \n\nShe sighs with relief and puts her left hand on her hip. “Comforting, don’t you think? That there are these places, these dark corners, where you can always find what you expect. Living there, though? That sounds awful, and always was,” she chuckles. “I bet the thugs of my youth are no longer around, so I wouldn’t count on them giving me a free pass. But I wish I could have a chance to drink a mug or two with the innkeeper once more. The old lady was always too good to stay in that muck.” "
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell2thais.rpy:830
    old "You tell her about the riots that happened two years after the invasion, led by hungry, ill people with no place to go. You describe briefly the streets that have risen from the ashes, but it doesn’t spark her interest. “I can’t say I {i}miss{/i} that place, but it’s weird to think that such a strong memory is no longer a part of reality. Like a tree that you’ve walked by a thousand times, and one day it’s been cut down.” She sits silent, absently observing your lips. "
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell2thais.rpy:838
    old "“Tell me, how do people dress in the city these days? Is it similar to what we have here? Before the war, the merchants were wearing those really long dresses and robes, way too long for my taste. They got mud stains after every rain, and I see no reason to keep shoes completely hidden.” "
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell2thais.rpy:838
    old "“Not anymore. There’s always a shortage of fabric. Most people wear tunics, like in the old days.”"
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell2thais.rpy:838
    old "“For years there was not enough hemp and wool at hand, so people have started to wear furs again.”"
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell2thais.rpy:838
    old "“As far as I can tell, many folks wear headgear.”"
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell2thais.rpy:838
    old "“I’m not sure. I don’t pay much attention to... {i}fashion{/i}.”"
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell2thais.rpy:845
    old "“At least we can hope that if the visitors arrive, we won’t stand out much!” She laughs, but also adjusts her dress, drawing your attention to its superb quality. “And who knows, maybe our little village here is going to help those unfortunate clothiers? I’m sure we could spare a couple of sheets of fabric.” "
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell2thais.rpy:854
    old "“Now, that’s just sad. When I was there, only the monks wore them, for... some reason. I’ve no doubt that the vengeful beasts have thrown the roads into a nightmare. The cityfolk would be smarter putting on rags.” Even though she sighs, there’s a cruel satisfaction in her smile. "
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell2thais.rpy:865
    old "You describe the complex world of veils, worn by rich folks who try to express their {i}modesty{/i} by covering their long hair; of hoods, which, thanks to the colorful embroidery, get fancier with every year; of light caps and heavier {i}turbans{/i} introduced by merchants from The Southern Realms. \n\n{color=#f6d6bd}The mayor{/color} has plenty of questions about colors, materials, prices... Only after you satisfy her curiosity does she let you change the topic, though still with shining eyes. "
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell2thais.rpy:876
    old "She pushes you with more detailed questions: What do the merchants wear? How about priests? Do armorers have enough linen and padding?” You struggle to say much, and she finally falls silent, observing you with annoyance. "
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell2thais.rpy:884
    old "“We talk and talk, but I still don’t know where you are from, [pcname]. What’s your story? Have you lived in {color=#f6d6bd}Hovlavan{/color} your entire life?” "
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell2thais.rpy:884
    old "“In a way. I know it as well as any other cityfolk, but every spring I trained in horsemanship in a nearby village.”"
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell2thais.rpy:884
    old "“Only for a bit. I was raised in a small village just nearby, and moved to the city after I had decided to look for luck as a roadwarden.”"
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell2thais.rpy:884
    old "“My past is already buried. Let’s not dig into it.”"
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell2thais.rpy:895
    old "“I was just about to ask about it! I couldn’t imagine someone building a stable and a paddock in a place where you can’t squeeze in a single new house. Your accent is very city-like, [custom1].” "
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell2thais.rpy:904
    old "“To see the city for the first time, after being surrounded by a couple of small houses and fields... It’s a strange feeling, isn’t it?” She puts her hand on the table. “Even after my second winter there I felt like a stranger. But those who know how to live in the countryside, close to the wilderness... We will always find a new home for ourselves, don’t you think?” She gives you an encouraging smile. "
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell2thais.rpy:913
    old "After a few heartbeats, she breaks the awkwardness with a smile. “And what else bothers you in the present?” "
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell2thais.rpy:921
    old "“I keep thinking... Surely, cityfolk don’t eat just wild game, salt fish, and groats. What animals do people breed in the nearby villages?” "
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell2thais.rpy:921
    old "“Mostly ibexes. They do well on the hills.”"
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell2thais.rpy:921
    old "“There’s a lot of mouflons. The monks need their parchment.”"
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell2thais.rpy:921
    old "“It depends. Mostly pond fish and fowl, but some can afford to buy boars.”"
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell2thais.rpy:921
    old "“There’s barely any meat, so people have started to raise crickets and rats.”"
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell2thais.rpy:921
    old "“Whatever people can buy, I guess. I don’t eat animals when I can avoid it.”"
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell2thais.rpy:928
    old "“So just like in the old days! I even saw some of them in the city, they are annoyingly good at climbing onto roofs and walls. But more importantly,” she adjusts her dress and smiles, “it means that our mouflon cheese and wool are going to be quite a commodity.” "
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell2thais.rpy:937
    old "“Oh, that’s terrible!” You catch a hint of annoyance in her laughter. “Our livestock won’t sell well! But that’s fine. It’s hard to keep the number of lambs high, we would need to sacrifice a field to raise a new flock.” "
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell2thais.rpy:946
    old "“Ah, {i}the meat of the tribes{/i}, yet as delicious as any. Our druids say that birds and fish are better for you than pork and mutton, would you believe? Even if they’re right, our {color=#f6d6bd}Creek{/color} has very little life in it, we rarely catch more than two fish a day.” "
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell2thais.rpy:954
    old "She covers her mouth. “I’ve tasted a few rats before, of course, but crickets? How do they taste?” "
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell2thais.rpy:954
    old "“It depends on the way you cook them and what you feed them with.”"
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell2thais.rpy:954
    old "“A bit like nuts, but they’re also ground into a {i}flour{/i}, of sorts. They’re good.”"
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell2thais.rpy:954
    old "“I don’t know. I don’t have a stomach for them. And they look disgusting.”"
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell2thais.rpy:960
    old "“Purely fascinating. At least now I know that if someone serves me a plate of insects, it’s not an affront,” she titters. “Though I do hope they don’t taste as good as mutton. I’m not going to sell our livestock cheap.” "
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell2thais.rpy:976
    old "She bursts into laughter. “Oh, butchering mouflons also isn’t pretty! I’m more than open to a little adventure. Maybe we should try to cook some on our own.” "
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell2thais.rpy:983
    old "“Oh, [pcname]! I believe you, but just indulge me. Listening about the city takes me back to the days when my bones were still strong.” "
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell2thais.rpy:1046
    old "She leans forward and even though she smiles, her voice is close to a whisper. “I wonder... Why are you here? What pushes someone to becoming a roadwarden?” "
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell2thais.rpy:1046
    old "“I need coin to help someone I care about.”"
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell2thais.rpy:1046
    old "“I’ll use the coins to retire early, in prosperity and safety.”"
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell2thais.rpy:1046
    old "“I need to build connections with the local leaders. I’ll be a new player in the merchant guild.”"
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell2thais.rpy:1046
    old "“I want to be remembered as the one who brought peace and order to this realm.”"
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell2thais.rpy:1046
    old "“I just want to help people. If I can make this area safer, I’m going to do it.”"
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell2thais.rpy:1046
    old "“A new life, that’s all I need. It doesn’t matter why.”"
