    # game/areas/howlersdell2thais.rpy:1053
    old "“Quite a burden! Many would turn to thievery, or plots, or blood magic. Your pursuit is... respectable.” She straightens up with an encouraging smile. “{color=#f6d6bd}Hovlavan{/color} is suffocating. All the churches, traders, soldiers, and craft guilds won’t welcome a stranger in need. Still...” she smirks, “better this than being an adventurer.” "
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell2thais.rpy:1061
    old "“Ah, the life of white bread and mead! Though even the richest cityfolk invest and work, one way or another. You can’t eat coins,” you catch a hint of mockery in her titter, “and you need more than a lock to protect yourself from envy and greed.” For a moment, she observes your palfrey. “Maybe move to a village? It’s easier to keep thieves away.” "
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell2thais.rpy:1070
    old "She gives you a wide, white grin. “A {i}healthy{/i} ambition, and a lovely one! With my weak bones, I couldn’t be a fighter, but with a few investments I sculpted a place for myself. If you want some advice from me,” she looks around, “remember your friends. Allies can carry you further than the heaviest pouch.” As she moves away, you once again notice the expensive rouge on her cheeks. "
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell2thais.rpy:1078
    old "“Such hubris!” You notice doubt in her brief laughter. “To think this place needs one’s touch, and even more so yours! I can’t {i}wait{/i} to see if you’re a soul led by a vision, or arrogance.” "
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell2thais.rpy:1086
    old "She waits, expecting that there’s more to be said, then lets out a nervous chuckle. “Forgive me, it’s something I mostly hear from children, not travelers.” She observes you with keen eyes, but after another few breaths, shrugs her doubts off. “What else do you need?” "
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell2thais.rpy:1094
    old "“So mysterious! But I understand. So you’re more of an adventurer than a soldier. I’d say it’s going to suit you well in the peninsula. One needs to know how to... Improvise.” There’s something uneasy about her smile. "
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell2thais.rpy:1150
    old "“So mysterious! But I understand. So you’re more of an adventurer, than a soldier. I’d say it’s going to suit you well in the peninsula. One needs to know how to... Improvise.” There’s something uneasy about her smile. "
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell2thais.rpy:1159
    old "“So mysterious! And rude!” While she laughs, her hand clenches around her buckle. “As you wish, dear roadwarden. Do you need anything else?” "
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell2thais.rpy:1167
    old "“You surely don’t avoid hard conversations, do you? Most cityfolk feel hesitant when they meet... {i}pagans{/i}.” She smirks, but the hand clenched around her deer-buckle makes you alert. “Are you that open to strangers, or did The United Church loosen its grasp? I’m interested in who could take their place. The guilds and artisans? The army?” "
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell2thais.rpy:1167
    old "I don’t like her assumptions. “I {i}don’t{/i} enjoy spending time with pagans, but I’m willing to look past our differences.”"
    new ""

    # game/areas/howlersdell2thais.rpy:1167
    old "“The United Church stands strong, and so do its laws. {color=#f6d6bd}Hovlavan{/color} is still loyal to the Empress, even if she’s not around.”"
