    old "“A compromise, then,” she gives you a habitual smile. “But the city’s attempts would never, ever end, not while we have anything they want. And yes, I’m ready to play their game, but are the other settlements? Will the next mayor of {color=#f6d6bd}Howler’s{/color} be able to handle this? If I sign a deal that pushes our children into chains twenty years from now, will I be responsible?” She looks at a nearby group that’s practicing a local song. "
