    old "For a few breaths, her green eyes seek something in your face. Her words are careful, yet hesitant. “She’s with the fogs now. The goblins were after food, so they carried her shell away. One day she’s going to charge at our walls, awoken and empty. Even though she was a bit... mawkish, her heart was strong, and patient. She listened to people, was ready to help them and to cry with them. I could tell you stories, but what for? Let the dead rest.” "
