    old "“Perfect! One more thing, though,” she puts her elbows on the table, leaning closer to you. “If you go behind my back, I’m not going to wait for a dagger. I’ll end you first.” \n\nShe rests her chin against her open palms, giving you a disarmingly warm smile. “I’m sure people already know that we have a {i}new{/i} roadwarden. Maybe ask around to see if anyone needs your help. The more my neighbors trust you and need you, the more willing they’ll be to offer you better pay.” "
