    old "“Are you serious? Where, exactly?” You tell her about your finding, though she hesitates to trust you. For a few long minutes she asks you for details, and you suddenly notice that a few of her questions are overlapping - she’s searching for lies. \n\nOnce satisfied, she gives you a grateful nod, crossing her legs and clasping her hands around the higher knee. “I can’t do anything with it before spring... But we’ll be prepared. Starting any work so close to the tribe from {color=#f6d6bd}Creeks{/color} won’t be easy, but I’ll figure this out.” "
